Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,...is mighty strange with her.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.42,0:00:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,She had always been a gymnastics enthusiast.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.73,0:00:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A sneaking suspicion arises in Truda:
Dialogue: 0,0:00:07.98,0:00:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Might she be actually Lotte?"
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.96,0:00:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,By chance, when she failed to talk her way through, \Nshe dispelled the doubts by saving a kid that fell into the river. {/luckily, ... she passed through the quandary} {to get over; to come through; to overcome (a difficulty)}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.87,0:00:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But at the same time, \NLuise was besieged by another major crisis.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:24.01,0:00:28.98,Sign,,0,0,120,,{\c&HBAF0F5&\bord0\blur0.8\fs20}Episode 14 \N {\fs35} I Can't Play the Piano {ピアノなんて弾けない} \N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N\N {\fs23} \h Translation: Perevodildo | Timings: Sub-RoRo \h
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.65,0:00:48.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Come on, Annie, one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.50,0:00:52.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.25,0:00:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Annie, almost there!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.41,0:00:57.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Even this clutz Lotte \Nwas able to do it! To the end!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.88,0:01:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so be it.{/enough}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.72,0:01:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie, you need to practice more.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.43,0:01:07.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Who asked you to shout all that out loud?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.40,0:01:08.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.41,0:01:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.70,0:01:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,but I really wasn't laughing at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.17,0:01:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, who {\i1}were{\i0} you laughing at, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.14,0:01:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Ouch-ouch-ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.17,0:01:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you won't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.15,0:01:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How many more times do I have to say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.08,0:01:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.56,0:01:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Your ineptitude on the horizontal bar \N can't be mitigated through blaming others! {/is not someone else's fault}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.52,0:01:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Ilse.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.83,0:01:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Gosh, she is annoying! \NNobody gets on my nerves like that! {/this behaviour is unforgivable}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.97,0:01:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's highly indecent of her to put on airs \Njust because she managed it herself once!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.44,0:02:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! There {\i1}has{\i0} to be something \NLotte is a complete bungler at!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.94,0:02:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll put our spines into finding it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.15,0:02:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, now the next page.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.70,0:02:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, this tune is something everyone should know. \NSchumann's Träumerei. {/dreaming}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.06,0:02:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, let's see, \Nwho should we ask to start...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.79,0:02:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte Körner.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.09,0:02:23.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.99,0:02:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Play it for us, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.16,0:02:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but how do I do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.61,0:02:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, with piano, obviously!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.44,0:02:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The one you have such a talent for.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.14,0:02:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? No, I'd rather...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.51,0:02:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! At long last, we'll hear Lotte's \Npiano play again! I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.17,0:02:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.97,0:02:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, let's hear it! {/play, play}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.24,0:02:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong with you two?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.05,0:02:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.65,0:02:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no... I'm supposed to know how to play it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.72,0:02:55.63,Default,,0,0,0,,They think I'm Lotte now, \Nthe prominent pianist!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.99,0:03:02.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but at the moment, \NI'm unable to play piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.43,0:03:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My... But what could be the reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.71,0:03:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.54,0:03:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I hurt my hand! {/hand hurts}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.77,0:03:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Impossible! Lotte was doing horizontal bar just an hour ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.18,0:03:18.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.22,0:03:21.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I was doing it for so long, \Nall my fingers went numb.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.46,0:03:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This won't do for a piano...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.00,0:03:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,My, is that so? If it starts hurting too much, \Ngo see the school doctor, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.93,0:03:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.25,0:03:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh well, I'll play it myself, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.36,0:03:34.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, eyes to the sheet music.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.66,0:03:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That's odd! She didn't hurt no hand!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.05,0:03:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead, she nearly hurt Annie \Nwhen pulled away her hand so brutally!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.90,0:03:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You think she malingers? \NI'll go there and expose her! {guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.97,0:03:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait! We can still leverage it. {/I had a good idea}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.25,0:03:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Annie! Silence, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.39,0:03:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Avoided it for now, somehow. Oh my, oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.95,0:04:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Odd!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.12,0:04:04.25,Default,,0,0,0,,She used to be beside herself when playing the piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.25,0:04:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And this excuse, too... The oddest of all! {/motive/pretext}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.23,0:04:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you lose sight of her!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.13,0:04:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,If there's any field Lotte is lacking in, \Nwe'll have it on our radar. {/find all the lotte's shortcomings}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.43,0:04:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? No way! \NI forgot to buy the butter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.17,0:04:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.22,0:04:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte Körner, are you not?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.11,0:04:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, it's been ages! \NHave you been well?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.05,0:04:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.12,0:04:35.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, who could that be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.39,0:04:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad I ran into you! I am now once again \Nliving in Munich, can you imagine?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.32,0:04:42.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad to see you again, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.46,0:04:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me, you still practice regularly, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.84,0:04:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Yes, I try to keep up with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.04,0:04:49.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Practice {\i1}what?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.69,0:04:53.54,Default,,0,0,0,,That is just dandy! This means \Nwe could renew our lessons right away!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.54,0:04:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I do? \NI've no clue what she's talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.21,0:04:58.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte never told me anything about it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.22,0:05:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter, Lotte? \NYou look disconcerted.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.77,0:05:03.39,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.39,0:05:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But could you tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.69,0:05:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Lessons... what about them? {joke here is that she prolly means "lessons of what" but teach thinks "lessons, when can we arrange the time?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.78,0:05:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that's right. \NWe'll just pick up where we left off.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.65,0:05:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Can start tomorrow already. \NIs that fine by you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.48,0:05:14.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Just...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.29,0:05:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll figure something out on the spot. \NGo for all or nothing! {take a chance; go for broke; nothing ventured, nothing gained}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.53,0:05:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Perfectly fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.60,0:05:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Splendid! Then, come to my place by three.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.01,0:05:23.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.31,0:05:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Excuse me, but your place is...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.88,0:05:27.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the same where I stayed before.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.65,0:05:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, I will be oh, so happy \Nto be able to teach you again!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.44,0:05:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Returning to Munich was a splendidly good idea!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.38,0:05:37.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to see your transformation\Ninto a marvelous pianist!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.09,0:05:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,A pianist?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.50,0:05:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be waiting for you tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.63,0:05:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh Lord!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.46,0:05:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.42,0:05:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.26,0:05:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you see, \NI was actually considering quitting piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.46,0:05:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.53,0:05:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, who gave you that most ridiculous idea?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.31,0:05:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,One way or another, I quit piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.08,0:06:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Goodbye!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.47,0:06:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.40,0:06:13.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I do know that woman! That was Frau Leitner! \NShe's giving piano lessons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.73,0:06:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a time I visited her, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.51,0:06:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Annie learned piano?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.25,0:06:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? You can play, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.09,0:06:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It was in the old days and only because dad asked me to!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.94,0:06:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I got bored of it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.61,0:06:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte also said she is quitting piano just now.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.34,0:06:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So suddenly... Odd, isn't it? \NThis and what she said during the music class. {really unsure about the last to ii mo to ii, would assume "time of music" to be time of the class}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.81,0:06:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte keeps feeding others the excuses \Nfor not playing the piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.10,0:06:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, we'll get to the bottom of this! {to determine (esp. a culprit or underlying cause); to pin down; to ascertain; to locate; to identify}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.63,0:06:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm... In the end, I'm thinking this one!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.04,0:06:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,No. Certainly, this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.84,0:06:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh no, it's too flashy! {(very) unusual; unconventional; eccentric; novel; original; striking; bizarre; wild}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.72,0:06:53.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It's your sense of style that is too out of date! {/old} {hope it's sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.26,0:06:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Körner, a phone call for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.64,0:06:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I redirected it your way.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.63,0:06:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.74,0:07:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Körner listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.21,0:07:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My, Frau Leitner!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.81,0:07:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, maybe this one, after all?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.20,0:07:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, though!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.54,0:07:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,My... Lotte said that?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.66,0:07:19.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well. I'll try to talk her out of it at once. \NThanks for letting me know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.27,0:07:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, it's settled.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.72,0:07:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Körner, we're using your photo.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.13,0:07:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Körner...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.56,0:07:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,She was always madly fond of piano... \NBut now, this?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.59,0:07:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Could she have acquired a distaste for it \Nafter learning about her dad's occupation? {/connected/related}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.10,0:07:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Miss Körner, we're making this photo \Nthe front cover. Agreed?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.38,0:07:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.31,0:07:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, you'll have to excuse me for an hour or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.80,0:08:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, I'd rather expect one to pick up the piano \Nupon discovering her dad is a musician. {not sure what she means: apart from ...; setting ... aside finding out her dad is mucisian, started playing piano}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.00,0:08:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Quitting it instead is counter-intuitive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.46,0:08:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.72,0:08:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.75,0:08:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah? What's the matter, mom? \NYou're back so soon today.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.55,0:08:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go there again in a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.37,0:08:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Lotte, you've met \Nwith Frau Leitner today, didn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.65,0:08:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah... Yes. What about it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.00,0:08:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,She called me in the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.01,0:08:32.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you really decline her lesson?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.99,0:08:35.09,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.09,0:08:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Before, you've been making such progress with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.39,0:08:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, Frau Leitner is back, at last.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.16,0:08:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you want to pick it back up?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.84,0:08:44.57,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so unnerving. \NHow should I explain it away?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.53,0:08:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, Lotte, you're not fretting \Nover minor bumps along the way, are you?{/you're not worrying about trifles  - not sure what she means}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.32,0:08:53.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Should you pick up the piano again, \NI'll also do my best to support that endeavor.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.89,0:08:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you need a piano to practice efficiently, \NI'll find a way around that, too. {/if a practice become troublesome without a piano}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.35,0:08:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh... No need, it's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.92,0:09:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not worried about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.88,0:09:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.28,0:09:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you this.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.65,0:09:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been born with an innate talent for music. {/talent}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.00,0:09:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's one of the things your mother takes pride in, \Nalong with a great joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.46,0:09:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing more important \Nthan leveraging that talent! {/I want you to expand/develop}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.40,0:09:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Please. Start taking lessons again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.92,0:09:24.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow, come to Frau Leitner's place. \NI'll let her know via a phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.21,0:09:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.37,0:09:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.53,0:09:30.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, I'm off.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.28,0:09:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be home early today.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.92,0:09:37.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll sort out the dinner, won't you,\Nmy little housekeeper?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.82,0:09:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a disaster. What do I do?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.87,0:10:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,My! Luise, everything's fine?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.83,0:10:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.56,0:10:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm home alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.13,0:10:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.35,0:10:07.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! Thank Goodness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.85,0:10:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I was trying to guess when would Resi go out.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.26,0:10:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Lotte. Need you to tell me something. Thing is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.76,0:10:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.18,0:10:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.25,0:10:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,That must have been Frau Leitner!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.33,0:10:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Frau Leitner?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.07,0:10:25.31,Default,,0,0,0,,She is a hearty and cordial lady,\Nwho used to teach me piano back in the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.31,0:10:28.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But about a year ago, her work \Nmade her leave for someplace far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.97,0:10:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't counting on her return, so I never told you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.74,0:10:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.02,0:10:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, she's back again? Glad to know!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.43,0:10:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Luise, don't you mean to say \NFrau Leitner told you to come take another lesson from her?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.36,0:10:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Bull's eye! Yes. That's exactly what she did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.84,0:10:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh?! What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.21,0:10:52.43,Default,,0,0,0,,She finds out you've suddenly unlearned to play piano - \Nthis doesn't bode well at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.43,0:10:55.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't worry, I'll employ all my talents to make it work. {no fucking clue: in that area, I'll show you how to do well}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.23,0:10:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ugh! Good gracious.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.97,0:11:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems, Resi just returned. \NTill later! Do your best.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.51,0:11:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually I managed to find my way around horizontal bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.38,0:11:11.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But now Luise and piano..?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.99,0:11:15.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope she makes it through.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.04,0:11:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,"I will,"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.89,0:11:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or so I'd like to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.36,0:11:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But still, I'm a complete piano layman.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.67,0:11:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in arithmetic, if you just study for dear life, \Nyou can get something done.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.86,0:11:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, next - shape the minced meat...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.92,0:11:36.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I was wrong by not taking it seriously \Nwhile I had the chance. {/in the past}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.96,0:11:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not how you do it, Luise. \NHow many more times do I have to say it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.42,0:11:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's better, once again now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.22,0:11:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.81,0:11:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you mean to say you haven't inherited \Neven a fraction of your dad's talent, Luise?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.61,0:12:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be the meddling of your mom's lousy genes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.13,0:12:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.76,0:12:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never want to play piano myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.31,0:12:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,My!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.19,0:12:16.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That lady was the worst of all!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.73,0:12:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, it seems to be true that dad's talent \Nwas wholly inherited by Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.56,0:12:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, so be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.59,0:12:26.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps, I have inherited some of mom's talents, instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.37,0:12:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, don't give up,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.83,0:12:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.84,0:12:35.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.60,0:12:42.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What a mess. {/failed/ruined}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.39,0:12:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, I guess I've no choice.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.19,0:13:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, she's even weirder than before!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.43,0:13:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Where do you think she's going?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.46,0:13:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,This seems to be the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.11,0:13:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, here goes nothing. {take a chance; go for broke; nothing ventured, nothing gained}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.53,0:13:27.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So she was going to Frau Leitner's place, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.91,0:13:29.79,Default,,0,0,0,,She's going to take piano lessons again? {/practice}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.79,0:13:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And yesterday, she said she won't! \NTotally strange! {/declined}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.16,0:13:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Been ages, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.20,0:13:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm certain that piano is delighted, too. \NLotte will finally be playing it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.00,0:13:43.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, won't you get straight to playing?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.27,0:13:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't wait to hear how much better \Nyou've grown in the last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.50,0:13:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But first...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.35,0:13:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I ask for a favor?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.36,0:13:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.39,0:13:54.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, I haven't actually been practicing with piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.01,0:13:57.05,Default,,0,0,0,,My! But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.82,0:14:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't tell you the reason as of yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.16,0:14:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to explain, but my lips are sealed. {/can't tell}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.95,0:14:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in the shortest term, \NI was planning to renew the practicing. {unsure: if a little bit more, I thought I'd start practicing again}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.83,0:14:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, I'd like to ask you to wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.77,0:14:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Good gracious, you must have \Na lot going on for you now.  {/intricate situation }
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.44,0:14:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.40,0:14:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I would have to ask you to tell mom \NI am attending the lessons like I'm supposed to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.44,0:14:24.31,Default,,0,0,0,,No need to give her extra worries now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.27,0:14:31.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Since Lotte is asking for this, \NI should think this is all for the greater good. {/I don't think I'm doing anything wrong}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.81,0:14:35.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, very well. \NI'll follow your instructions to the letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.29,0:14:36.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.66,0:14:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But in exchange, as soon as you're able to tell me the reason, \Nyou'll give me the whole story, start-to-end!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.82,0:14:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh... I'm dying to know, \Nso please don't take too long! {no clue what's hasuzui, would assume "can't wait for"}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.92,0:14:46.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.15,0:14:54.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't hear a thing. No piano playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.13,0:14:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,What is she doing there?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.31,0:14:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! She's back! Lotte's coming!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.90,0:15:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it! Talked my way through, somehow! {same word as in the narrator's review of last episode - to get over; to come through; to overcome (a difficulty)}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.81,0:15:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Yahoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.52,0:15:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,What just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.47,0:15:29.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have a single clue what had happened, \Nbut it seems, Lotte can no longer play piano.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.43,0:15:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Just forgot it or something, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.65,0:15:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like Miria forgot how to do arithmetic! {guess, I hear "miria ano sansuu ja arumaishi" - still unsure what name could it be and it's clear now that it's not a variation of miriam, jaarumaishi seems to mean "well it couldn't be because of ..., right?" but then I've no clue why she says "miryam's math" if they're talking about lotte forgetting it, or whatever the hell this first word is... oh god.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.04,0:15:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,She forgot how to play piano, that's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.52,0:15:44.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But hey, when you learn piano, \Nisn't it written to that part of your brain
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.22,0:15:47.49,Default,,0,0,0,,that cannot be rewritten, \Nno matter what happens to you? {again, no fucking clue: inside your head, the place that remembers piano, whatever becomes of it, doesn't forget}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.49,0:15:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I've also heard of this another thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.39,0:15:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,like when you fall from a cliff, \Nthen wake up not even remembering who you are! {nor anyone else}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.30,0:15:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now {\i1}that{\i0} must be it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.07,0:15:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte had suffered an amnesty! {/memory ... - any word similar to what's supposed to be "loss"} {souseiji is "twins" so I'm thinking if this is a pun on how she guessed it right by guessing it wrong somehow}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.74,0:16:00.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's called amnesia, Annie.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.84,0:16:02.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.48,0:16:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, there's the fact Lotte \Ncompletely forgot how to play the piano!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.55,0:16:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, that spells fun!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.78,0:16:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that manner, \NI had also safely talked my way through the crisis. {on my end}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.27,0:16:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, aren't we two the lucky bunch?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.85,0:16:33.94,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I shall be henceforth praying \Nthat I'm not asked to play piano during the music classes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.94,0:16:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,And you should pray, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.02,0:16:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,My, this Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.61,0:16:52.49,Default,,0,0,0,,That said, the day we two finally return to our usual places \Nis certainly becoming quite the wild ride for everyone else. {complex; complicated; intricate; mixed (feelings)}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.99,0:16:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.76,0:16:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Luise!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.30,0:17:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! What great news I have!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.09,0:17:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going for an unforeseen trip. {lit: suddenly there's a need to travel}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.30,0:17:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,With Luise in tow!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.64,0:17:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,A trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.96,0:17:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,When?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.76,0:17:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, dear!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.82,0:17:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, start packing now.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.85,0:17:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Resi! Resi!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.05,0:17:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So suddenly... At least tell me where to!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.38,0:17:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Give me just a moment!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.52,0:17:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry up! We're late for the train!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.69,0:17:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I need to tell Luise as soon as possible! {/I should let luise know sooner}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.13,0:17:38.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Please reach her in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.68,0:17:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, everyone, quiet now!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.98,0:17:59.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Our trip to cinema, scheduled for tomorrow, \Nis getting postponed!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.82,0:18:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,What? Unfair! {/boring}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.25,0:18:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But to not leave you without a treat, \Nwe're holding a records-listening party, instead. {/in exchange for that I thought I want to hold a special showing; screening; viewing party of records}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.03,0:18:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody cares about the records!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.00,0:18:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Bo-o-oring!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.41,0:18:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Teacher!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.68,0:18:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it, Annie?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.58,0:18:25.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why settle on records, when we can listen \Nto some live performances, instead? {/I think ... are better than ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.61,0:18:33.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got some people here really adroit with piano, \Nwhy don't we cooperate with them to hold a mini-concert?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.49,0:18:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,My, that also sounds very good. \NBut who do we ask to do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.76,0:18:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,No doubt about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.53,0:18:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,that must be Lotte Körner!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.22,0:18:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw shuuucks!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.30,0:18:44.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.33,0:18:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,This is all... so sudden.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.70,0:18:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Maria supports it, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.83,0:18:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So does Miria!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.03,0:18:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I support!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.80,0:18:51.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I know Lotte won't let us down!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.97,0:18:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The class representative, \Nshow them what you're made of!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.91,0:19:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,We got her! This paves the way \Nfor Lotte's grand embarrassment!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.22,0:19:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.92,0:19:17.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't joke with such things!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.79,0:19:41.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.43,0:19:44.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Answer the phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.53,0:19:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,This is important!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.57,0:19:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as she talked her way out of one crisis, \NLuise is watching helplessly
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.24,0:20:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,at an even bigger crisis \Nunfolding before her eyes. {/waiting for her}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.69,0:20:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,She tries to get some help with it, \Nbut Lotte is out of reach. {/consult}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.67,0:20:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Once again, Luise's heart sinks in desperation. {again this "chest is about to be crushed; to be squashed; to be smashed; to be destroyed; to be broken; to collapse" but I don't remember how I translated it last time}
Comment: 0,0:20:19.12,0:20:19.12,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.06,0:20:28.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,A miserable romance {可哀想ね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.59,0:20:32.05,Sign,,0,0,0,,A tear-jerking nuance {涙誘うニュアンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.05,0:20:35.77,Sign,,0,0,0,,If you turn another page of your memories, {想い出のページめくれば}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.77,0:20:38.68,Sign,,0,0,0,,Here she is - heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン} {actually, "the heroine of the recollections" but that doesn't have a nice ring to it}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.90,0:20:50.32,Sign,,0,0,0,,I raise my eyes to your face - {あなたの面影　見上げて咲いている}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.32,0:20:54.08,Sign,,0,0,0,,Suddenly, I'm in full bloom {unsure, maybe "it's flourishing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.08,0:20:57.62,Sign,,0,0,0,,A sunflower amidst the blizzard - {act. in the middle of winter}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.62,0:21:01.02,Sign,,0,0,0,,that would be me, my dear {真冬のひまわり　それが私なの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.46,0:21:04.19,Sign,,0,0,0,,Always on the verge of freezing, {凍えるような気持ちでいつも}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.04,0:21:07.59,Sign,,0,0,0,,My feelings are out of control -
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.59,0:21:12.14,Sign,,0,0,0,,Too stiff to even say "Do you still love me?" {「好き?」と尋くこともできず}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.14,0:21:16.29,Sign,,0,0,0,,My lips just keep wavering in this wind! {風に揺れていたわ}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.84,0:21:21.49,Sign,,0,0,0,,A pitiful Romance {いじらしいね　ロマンス}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.49,0:21:24.90,Sign,,0,0,0,,Something that only happens in dreams: {夢のような出来事}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.90,0:21:28.53,Sign,,0,0,0,,Trying hard to forget, I fell even more in love {忘れるために愛したの}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.53,0:21:31.30,Sign,,0,0,0,,with heroine of the past {追憶のヒロイン}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.35,0:21:36.12,Sign,,0,0,0,,Miracle that I came across now is hugging me tight {めぐりあえた奇跡　そっと抱きしめて}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.12,0:21:39.53,Sign,,0,0,0,,This is the story of my life, I'll do my best to protect it! {私だけの歴史　守ってゆくわ}
Comment: 0,0:21:43.12,0:21:43.12,Sign,,0,0,0,,{chapter}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.38,0:21:44.88,Sign,,0,0,0,,Next episode
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.32,0:21:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The day of the mini-concert is finally here!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.85,0:21:55.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be that Annie and others \Nhave gotten a lead that I might not be the real Lotte!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.09,0:21:57.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Luise, don't you have one of your usual "good ideas?"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.15,0:21:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a single one!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.55,0:22:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in murky waters, then!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.89,0:22:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,If only Lotte could come here somehow, \Nit all would be set straight again!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.26,0:22:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, why? Why is this happening to me?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.59,0:22:10.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time in I and Myself: Lotte, Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.96,0:22:12.66,Sign,,0,0,0,,Episode 15 \NLotte, Help!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.40,0:22:11.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Help, somebody!
